	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>THE SHADOW FALLS:TWILIGHT CHAPTER 6</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><html>

<head>
<meta http-equiv="Content-Type"
content="text/html; charset=iso-8859-1">
<title>Untitled </title>
</head>

<body>

<p>------------------------------------<br>
Chapter 6. Scorched Earth<br>
------------------------------------<br>
<br>
After several hard days journey the trio arrives at the gates of
Qeynos, the shining human citadel. After being on<br>
their guard for bounty hunters and the like for all this time.
They are glad to be safe within the cities confines. As with<br>
any normal day Qeynos is alive with the bustle of traders, street
performers and the common folk.<br>
<br>
Leylia is awestruck with the size and majesty of the city, and
begins to wander around aimlessly absorbing the sights.<br>
Reyas grudgingly pursues still rather grumpy over the forced form
change.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;Wow! It's so big! It makes Felwithe seem so tiny by
comparison! And there are so many people!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah well, they don't call it the Gem of Antonica for
nothing.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Stop being so grumpy, we are almost to Odus and we have the
other Twilight child. What could possibly be wrong!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You're not the one stuck with being a girl for the last 7
days!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But I am a girl, silly&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You know what I mean. This stupid swishy hair and this
stupid dress and these enormous...&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;HEY! Guys wait up for me!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tenrou trotted up to them from the guard station at the gate.<br>
<br>
&quot;You guys where just going to leave me?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes. Least I would do to you for this stupid idea.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;At least it got us here. I don't like this Human illusion
any more then you like being a girl. But it got us away from the<br>
bounty hunters.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Which we wouldn't have even needed to do, if some one
hadn't been such a lousy thief! Hey!!!! Who pinched me!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You should have used an uglier form. Looks like you're
getting admirers.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why me?&quot;<br>
<br>
Reyas storms off into the crowd.<br>
<br>
&quot;That reminds me Leylia. I have to make my report to the
Qeynos Council.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Leaving us already?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not really. I want to go talk to my grandfather
first.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So the lone rogue has a gentle side?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You don't know my grandfather. But first, lets go find
Reyas before he ends up hurting the next person that flirts with<br>
him.&quot;<br>
-------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey there Cutey! Want to go have some fun?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why you! I'm going to!!!&quot; Reyas gets ready to spring
on the unknowing pub patron when the others intercept him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are way to high strung Reyas.&quot;<br>
<br>
'I can't take this much longer&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't worry. Once I go make my report to the Council, we
will be fine and you can shift back.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So why are you still here?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I am looking for my grandfather. He is around here
somewhere. He can always be found somewhere near one of<br>
these pubs.&quot;<br>
<br>
Putting his arms around Leylia and Reyas they continue to walk
around the city center meandering from pub to pub.<br>
Looking for his grandfather without much luck. As the day begins
to drift away, news reaches them of a new pub that is<br>
opening that night. Continuing on to the club, they discover that
is quite packed and alive with the sounds of dozens of<br>
bards playing and hundreds of people having a great time.<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't understand. A brand new night pub and Granpa Tico
isn't here? It's not like him. O well. At least I have me two<br>
favorite women with me!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Grr! One woman! Get that through your head!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah yeah&quot;<br>
<br>
A voice comes from behind them just audible over the loud music
blaring.<br>
<br>
&quot;How like you to keep all the prettiest girls all to
yourself.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;GRANPA!&quot; Tenrou turns to face a small older man
surrounded by several fairly attractive younger women.<br>
<br>
&quot;But this old man still has quite a few tricks left up his
sleeve! Allow me to introduce you to Miss, Qeynos! Miss Freeport,<br>
Miss Felwithe and Miss Kelethin! HAHAAAHA!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Same old Granpa! Great to see you!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Same to you my boy! I take it things went well in
Neriak?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Very well. I found out something interesting too. Lets go
find somewhere a little quieter to discuss it.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;A good idea! If you will excuse me ladies, I have business
to discuss.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh. Don't go!&quot;<br>
&quot;Stay Tico!&quot;<br>
&quot;We will miss you too much!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ladies! Ladies! I will be back that is assured.&quot;<br>
<br>
The small scene reminds him that he hasn't introduced the others
to his grandfather, so he starts to turn back to them.<br>
&quot;Hey guys, this my granpa....Guys? Where'd you go?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I think you're skills at keeping women needs improving
M'boy.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;So it seems. I'll catch up with them later. We have much to
talk about Granpa.&quot;<br>
------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Unknown to Tenrou, Reyas thoroughly fed up with being hit on,
shifted back to his male form. But had also lost track of<br>
Leylia.<br>
<br>
/Leylia. Where are you?/<br>
<br>
Hehe. You'll see<br>
<br>
/Leylia./<br>
<br>
Trust me.<br>
<br>
At that moment the music playing in the club stopped playing, and
the manager could be heard. <br>
<br>
&quot;Guess what everyone. As a special surprise for our grand
opening. We have a sweet little Elven girl come all the way<br>
from Faydwer, just to give us a show we'll never forget!&quot;<br>
<br>
/Leylia..you didn't.../<br>
<br>
&quot;Start the music!&quot;<br>
<br>
The magic lamps in the pub go out and the bards begin to gently
play some soft sitar music. Several directional wisp<br>
lamps shine on the center stage and a well-tanned elf shrouded in
silken garments enters the stage. She begins to<br>
dance slowly with the sitars, the silken drapes flowing through
the air mimicking her movements. Reyas along with the<br>
rest of the crowd, is silent enraptured with her.<br>
<br>
/\Wow. She looks so..perfect./\<br>
<br>
The bards begin to smoothly pick up the tempo and switch to other
instruments. Leylia continues with them increasing<br>
her movements.<br>
----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;So that old wives tale is true?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes. As it seems, the darker girl is the other
Dragoon&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And what of the other girl&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;She isn't really a girl.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Why I had no idea Tenrou.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Huh? O No! No! She..er. he is a familiar; we had him switch
shape so we wouldn't attract any bounty hunters on our<br>
way from Highpass. We ..uh..ran into a little trouble
there.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I know.&quot; Tico removes a small wanted poster from his
robes. On it states <br>
<br>
Wanted: Male Human. Petty Theft and resisting arrest 1000
Platinum coins.<br>
<br>
It has a badly drawn picture of Tenrou with his human illusion
ring on.<br>
<br>
&quot;Word does spread fast doesn't it. Ehe..oh boy..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You got careless Tenrou. You should have packed more
supplies before you left Neriak.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Well I hadn't planned on leaving as soon as I did, but
that's no excuse.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No, it isn't. But at least you are ok. With the information
you have acquired. We will be able to make great.....&quot;<br>
<br>
A bright flash of light shines through the window of the room,
followed a few seconds later by 2 more. Then one more a<br>
moment later, this time accompanied by a loud boom, which rattled
the house.<br>
<br>
&quot;What the!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Tenrou! Report to the castle immediatly! I will investigate
this.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Do it!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes sir.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And Tenrou..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Take care of those two. You have a big future in front of
you, you are going to need all the help you can get.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Granpa.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And one more thing.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Take off that silly illusion ring.&quot;<br>
<br>
Happily Tenrou complies, the human visage around him flickers for
a moment then winks away. Leaving his true form.<br>
<br>
&quot;Much better Tenrou. Now get going!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright!&quot;<br>
---------------------------------------<br>
<br>
As Leylia continued to entice the crowd, several men got rather
uppity and began to create a disturbance.<br>
<br>
&quot;YEAH! Shake that thing for us!&quot;<br>
&quot;Show us what's underneath there!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey! Show a little respect you loathsome knuckle
heads!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey!! Shut up platinum top!&quot; One of the men picked up
a chair and hurled it at Reyas, missing him by a long distance,
but<br>
the chair careened into the bards stopping the show. The wisp
lamps then went out.<br>
<br>
&quot;See what You've done! You've made my dancing lovely stop!
Savages&quot; someone called out from the dark pub. Then all<br>
the lamps came on, and behind Leylia was a tall man with large
ethereal wings.<br>
<br>
&quot;Leylia move away!&quot;<br>
<br>
She tried too but he caught her the edge of her garments and
tripped her. Just as she was about to hit the ground,<br>
Reyas caught her in his arms.<br>
<br>
&quot;You ok Leylia?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm fine. If I could get this stupid dress off, I could
give him a good beating.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Leave that to me. This is guy is has Veeshan's crest on his
chest plate. I don't want anything to happen to you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;But..&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;There will be no buts, except yours leaving this pub. Now
go!&quot; He quickly slashes the trapped garments and rights<br>
Leylia. &quot;Besides. I have been wanting a chance to show
off.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Alright, be careful.&quot; She hops of the stage and heads
out through the crowd towards the door. Reyas turns back to the<br>
winged figure.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now you. Before I kill you, what is your name so I know
which of Veeshan's lackeys have fallen before me.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You boast much boy. I am Sirandael. Veeshan's guardian of
the winds. Now let's see what your made of. BLADE<br>
WIND!&quot; <br>
<br>
A crescent of energy leapt out slicing through the stage only
towards Reyas and at the last moment it is knocked away,<br>
arcing above the heads of the patrons and blasting out one of the
walls of the pub.<br>
<br>
&quot;HA! If that's all Veeshan can hire, then conquering her
will be easy. Now it's my turn&quot; Extending his hand out a<br>
broad-sword shaped mana blade formed in it. Gripping it tightly
it began to glow, making the pub fill with light.<br>
<br>
&quot;GRAVITY SLASH!&quot;<br>
<br>
Anyone who was still in the pub was momentarily blinded by the
attack. When their sight cleared, the street was in the<br>
place of the stage, the attack blasting away that part of the
pub.<br>
<br>
&quot;OOO. Those two idiots just wrecked my brand new night pub!
I'LL GET YOU MAN!&quot;<br>
------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Tico entered the guard tower, high above in the city wall. Below
part of the walls of Qeynos were scorched, having<br>
being touched by incendiaries. On closer inspection, there was a
garrison of troups following a small cart. On the cart<br>
was priest wielding a large pointed staff, he was standing over a
soldier who had been chained down to the floor of the<br>
cart. The design of the soldier armor indicated that he was a
general of the Qeynos army.<br>
<br>
&quot;By the gods. Isn't that!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's General Goron!&quot;<br>
<br>
The commotion outside the walls had attracted much attention and
the city walls were filled with civilians and Qeynos<br>
troops.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey!! those are Freeport uniforms! But why do they have
those claw designs scratched on their breastplates?&quot; The<br>
people began to murmur as the scene below. The answer to their
questions came very soon, as the priest turned to the<br>
wall and raised his staff. Making sure everyone saw the pointed
end of it, then he rammed into the shoulder of the<br>
General, his scream followed closely. The priest began to move it
around jerkingly and viscously spraying blood all over<br>
the cart and troops behind it.<br>
<br>
The crowds above were shocked. They could only listen in horror
as the priest began to speak.<br>
<br>
&quot;Listen to the cries of your pagan general, People of
Qeynos! Hear as the goddess Veeshan enters his body and<br>
teaches him a lesson for praying to false gods! Open you're gates
so that her light might spare you from eternal<br>
suffering!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What in the hell are they doing! No one deserves this!
Especially no the General&quot; <br>
<br>
More of his cries echo out in the night as the cart circles the
city. The priest continues his torture viscously. Then the<br>
general manages to break through the pain and begins to call out
to the people of Qeynos.<br>
<br>
&quot;Listen my people! Do not be swayed by their actions! They
torture me to break your will and to gain access to our fair<br>
city to destroy it! Do not listen to them! Stand tall. I ask that
one of you pierce my heart with an arrow so that I might die<br>
with digni....AAAAAHHHHHH!!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
The priest's staff rips into his face, cutting out part of his
tongue and lips, then enters his abdomen.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hear how the coward cries and begs for mercy. But Veeshan
shall punish him for his crimes! We shall rip off his<br>
fingers and toes, his arms and legs! Surrender now people of
Qeynos and maybe Veeshan will have mercy upon you!&quot;<br>
-------------------------<br>
<br>
&quot;You're late Tenrou.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I had business to discuss with grandfather. And got held
up.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That's no excuse. Besides you know better then to talk to
senile old fool.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;He's not senile!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Silence boy! You have failed us! Your information is
outdated and you did not procure any of the needed herbs from<br>
Neriak!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I tried! There just isn't any left in Neriak!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Lies! All lies! You just wish to see her die, so be it
Tenrou. Her blood is on your hands!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You ! You! How can some one as cold and uncaring as you be
a paladin, let alone good enough for mother! What could<br>
she possibly see in a dog like you!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Silence you insolent child!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I will not be quiet! I will no longer stay under your heel,
to be ground down like an insect!&quot; Tenrou thumbs his
sheathed<br>
sword, ready to strike.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I guess I should beat some sense into you boy. It's
about time I removed you from your mother's breast.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tenrou dashed forward his blade flashing out, but before he could
get close enough to strike, a page interrupted by<br>
bursting into the room.<br>
<br>
&quot;M'lord Jacin!! The city is under siege!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;What!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;General Goron has been captured and is currently being
tortured by the Freeport Militia. And a few moments ago<br>
several of the Militia began to toss oil flasks at the
wall.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;The Freeport Militia? Where are they know?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Circling the city walls. As far as we can see, there is one
contingent up front, but we suspect several more hiding in the<br>
hills.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Sound the alarm, have the civilians fall back inside the
castle. I want the towers and wall garrisoned as of 5 minutes<br>
ago.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes sir!&quot;<br>
<br>
The page exits the room in a rush nearly stumbling over himself.
Jacin turns back to Tenrou, then heads out the door.<br>
<br>
&quot;We aren't through here Tenrou. We will deal with this after
the Militia has been crushed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Agreed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Go to the dining hall and wait. Queen Maoryani will be down
there shortly, escort her through the Sewers and out to the<br>
safety of the Surefall Glades.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I am not yours to order around.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I don't have time to argue with you. Just do it. I will
beat you for dissent later.&quot; And he ended it by exiting the
room.<br>
<br>
&quot;Damn you.&quot;<br>
------------------------------------<br>
<br>
The blood spilled freely as Reyas yanked out his blade from the
center of Sirandael. Sirandael hovered in the air for a<br>
moment, then plummeted to the ground 90 feet below. As they mana
blade flickered and disappeared, his gaze walked<br>
over to the city wall of Qeynos, which was now in turmoil. Much
of the area surrounding the wall was in flames, and<br>
there were fierce battles taking place all through it.<br>
<br>
Reyas's eyes began to glow a light blue and his vision sharpened
and zoomed in on the action-taking place. He quickly<br>
recognized the insignia of the Qeynos troops and that off the
attackers.<br>
<br>
/\Freeport Militia? How could they have gotten here so fast? An
army that size would create a lot of ruckus , and they<br>
couldn't have been that far behind us./\<br>
<br>
Then the breastplate of one of the Militia troops came into his
view for a second.<br>
<br>
/\Veeshan. I should have known. She must have. What power. Too
move, so many, so far, so quickly. Could Leylia<br>
possibly have that much power to frighten Veeshan so much? How
could a perfect girl like her be capable of../\<br>
<br>
An explosion rips a hole in the wall surrounding Qeynos and
hundreds of screaming Militia pour through it. At the head of<br>
the wave, was a woman. She was blond haired and her face was
covered by a golden ceramic mask. On her back<br>
were the telltale wings; she was a another one of Veeshan's
heralds. She easily cast aside dozens of brave Qeynos<br>
troops who tried to stop the influx of enemies. Then to Reyas's
horror he saw a dark skinned girl charge toward the<br>
herald, wielding two blades.<br>
<br>
&quot;LEYLIA NOO!!!&quot;<br>
---------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
The sounds of the battle boomed through the dark sewers
underneath Qeynos, in which Tenrou and the Queen were<br>
silently navigating through. The Queen was having a silent
struggle trying to keep up with Tenrou, keeping herself<br>
covered underneath the silken shrouds, and trying not to step
into something.<br>
<br>
&quot;You know you shouldn't strain yourself.&quot;<br>
<br>
She makes no acknowledgement of him.<br>
<br>
&quot;You must really be tired keeping this act up. We should
stop and let you rest.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Wha.. how did you see through my disguise!?!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Easy! Your perfume. Everyone smells different even if they
use the same perfume. Not too mention, that this is the same<br>
time of shannigans that my idiot father would put me up too.
While we put our lives on the line as decoys, the real queen<br>
is probably off taking bath or getting her nails done. Such a
typical attitude of nobles like them, expect us to do all the do<br>
the hard work and get thanked with misery.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Silence! I won't let you talk ill of Lord Jacin or Queen
Maoryani!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah, Yeah.&quot; Tenrou turns away holding his torch out
toward the darkness.<br>
<br>
&quot; What ever hostility you harbor for them, is of your on
accord. I am glad to serve my queen in any way possible!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, what a fine slave! The nobility can afford to be
arrogant and conceited, because they have such loyal, devoted<br>
slaves. But they give nothing back. Suffering is your only
reward. Excuse me if I refuse to be a part of that.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; So I take it, you won't escort me any further?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot; My orders were to escort the Queen. Not a syllable was
mentioned about escorting a servant impersonating the queen.<br>
So if you don't mind, I'll take my leave.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
The servant lashes out at Tenrou with a small dagger which had
been hidden in her sleeve.<br>
<br>
&quot;IMPETULANT CHILD!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tenrou easily dodges the servants' wild swings<br>
<br>
&quot;Stop that! Take it easy. I might be disrespectful, but I
have no desire to fight a servant girl!&quot;<br>
<br>
She lunges at him again; with a quick motion he knocks away, and
captures her hands underneath his arm, so he could<br>
hold onto her and the torch. She then slams her knee into his
groin, forcing him to let go of both.<br>
<br>
While Tenrou reels, she snatches up the torch and dashes of into
the distance turning left at the nearby corner.<br>
<br>
&quot;ahhh.. Wait! Not..that.. way! You're going the wrong
way!&quot;<br>
<br>
A few moments later she cries out and a distorted voice follows
her cry.<br>
<br>
&quot;How sad this realm is, that it's ruler abandons it with out
a struggle.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Lord Caryoon! What are you doing with the invaders?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Lord Caryoon!?! That's the way a servant speaks, that's not
Queen Maoryani!&quot;<br>
<br>
A sound of air being cut and the splash of something heavy
entering the sewage reaches Tenrou. A moment later, her<br>
body floats past him. 7 figures come around the corner. 4 of them
are of the Freeport Militia. One is wearing the insignia<br>
of Qeynos. The last has no visible insignia, he is shrouded in
cloak and wearing a silver-horned mask.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's far enough! What kind of devil are you to kill a
simple girl doing her job! Lets see how big you are now!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tenrou thumbs his blade out of its sheath and wades through the
sewage toward them.<br>
The silver masked one speaks, his voice slightly distorted by his
mask. &quot;Caryoon, deal with this trash, then rejoin me on<br>
the surface.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes Silver Mask.&quot;<br>
<br>
Caryoon and his men circle Tenrou swords drawn and ready, and
Silver Mask continues on. Caryoon points his bloody<br>
blade at Tenrou. <br>
<br>
&quot;Kill him.&quot;<br>
<br>
The men charge.<br>
<br>
ONE! &quot;AAAAAAAA!!&quot;<br>
TWO! &quot;GWAAAA!!!&quot;<br>
THREE! &quot;AAARGH!&quot;<br>
FOUR!! &quot;AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And FIVE!&quot; Tenrou exclaims as he dispatches them. He
sheaths his blade just as the bodies' splash into the sewage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Now, I wonder where metal head has run off too.&quot;<br>
--------------------------<br>
<br>
Leylia's blades drank well of the blood of the dozens of Militia
she dispatched. All of which tried to stop her from<br>
reaching the herald of Veeshan. <br>
<br>
Soon as she got close to the Herald, another person moved up
beside her. An old man, from his fighting stance obviously<br>
a monk.<br>
<br>
&quot;Who are you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm your friend's Grandpa. Tico Bishou&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Your Tenrou's grandfather?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;That's right! Now pretty thing watch as this old man shows
off a few of his tricks!&quot;<br>
<br>
Tico dashes right into the fray casting aside the Militia, then
launching himself into the air to perform a thunderous flying<br>
kick on the herald. But the Herald grabs hold of his foot, twirls
him above her head and then tosses him into a nearby<br>
wall, creating a large crater in it.<br>
<br>
&quot;You weaklings are no match for Nagi.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Tico!&quot; Leylia snapped to a ready position, but got
interrupted again as someone else got in front of her. Reyas.<br>
<br>
&quot;Move out of my way Reyas!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Not a chance! Get out of her! I'll deal with her!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Damn it stop, babying me!&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm doing this for your protection. I made a promise and
I..&quot;<br>
<br>
He stopped midway and attacked Nagi. Leylia fell back towards to
the castle.<br>
---------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Tenrou's blade shattered as it was hit by the energy wave. The
wave him picked up and slammed him through one of the<br>
castle pillars.<br>
<br>
A distorted voice called out to him. &quot;A fair try child, but
your skills lack greatly. Now it is time for you to die.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;DEMONS DANCE!&quot; <br>
<br>
Silver Mask was knocked back but still upright by the surprise
attack. He turned to face his attacker.<br>
<br>
&quot;So we meet again Twilight child.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Silver Mask.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Like your friend, you should prepare your soul for the next
life.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You should take your own advice!&quot; Leylia attacked him
with everything she had, her blades sounding loudly in the main<br>
hall of the castle, as they collided with Silver Mask's sword. <br>
<br>
Silver Mask easily parried her attacks and knocked one of her
blades away, then planting a foot in her sternum.<br>
<br>
She reeled backwards, the wind in her lungs leaving her. A sharp
blow to her head flings her against one of the walls.<br>
Completely dazed and helpless, Leylia can only watch has his
blade begins to glow; he raises it above his head and then<br>
slams it to the ground. The ground in front of the blade ripped
apart, and tore toward her. In another second her body<br>
was wracked with pain. Her body exhausted, collapsed to the
floor. She could not move has the heavy plod of metal<br>
boots came toward her. A boot rolled her over, and she stared up
at Silver Mask. He clutched his sword with both hands<br>
and held it above her. She closed her eyes and waited for death
to embrace her.<br>
<br>
<br>
But she received only pain, blunt pain as something dug into her.
Forcing out blood and air at the same time. She gagged<br>
and reeled as the pain ripped through her every nerve. It took
her a moment to realize that she still lived and that Silver<br>
Mask was gone. She reached up to her chest, the source of the
pain and felt something small and round. Her pendant. It<br>
was cracked.<br>
----------------------------------<br>
<br>
(*Angel With One Wing. Final Fantasy 7 Sound Track)<br>
<br>
Nagi held still unsure of what to do, only a moment before the
child in front of her, was putting up an amazing struggle,<br>
almost to her level of skill. Now he was on his knees clutching
his chest in pain. His eyes flashed a bright white and he<br>
began to shout something<br>
<br>
&quot;NOE'ES DRAKAIN AL SHAE VAL LIBERYAL AR TO LURER
AIRE!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
The boy stood up no longer in pain; his whole body alit with
power. The ground that he stood on burned at his touch. He<br>
held out one of his arms flexing it, admiring himself.<br>
<br>
/\The pendant it's damaged, I should be dying. But instead every
fiber of my being is rippling with../\ <br>
<br>
&quot;POWER!!!&quot; He threw a fist at Nagi and even though he
was not even close enough to touch, she was hurled backward<br>
by an unseen force. Nagi then began to lift into the air, clawing
madly at an invisible hand around her throat. Her body<br>
shudder violently and blood splashed on the ground as, unseen
hands impacted against her body. All the while Reyas,<br>
stood in place admiring himself. Her mask cracked and bloodied,
Nagi found herself being thrown, like a rag doll and<br>
bouncing of walls and buildings. Eventually the invisible hand
let her go and she plummeted to the ground and moved no<br>
more.<br>
<br>
Reyas laughed, staring into the sky. &quot;I REMEMBER EVERYTHING
VEESHAN! YOU WILL DIE!!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
As if too respond the heavens began to crack and blow with the
sounds of an oncoming storm.<br>
--------------------------------<br>
With the amulet that holds Reyas's life essence cracked, he
should on the brink of death, but instead his power is<br>
multiplying by an unknown fold. With this new development, one
must wonder if there far more to him then can be seen.<br>
But even with his newfound power is he strong enough to defeat
Silver Mask and save Leylia? And why does the<br>
herald of Veeshan continue to spare Leylia's life? Find out as
the battle for Qeynos continues and the mysteries of<br>
Twilight unfold in the next chapter of The Shadow Falls!<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
------------------------------<br>
Preview of the Next Chapter (Spoiler Alert!)<br>
------------------------------<br>
<br>
The battle to save Qeynos from destruction continues, and now it
seems that Reyas with his unlocked powers are<br>
giving Silver Mask a run for his money. But just when hope seems
to have succeeded, it turns out that Nagi isn't down<br>
for the count after all! Will Reyas be able to deal with both of
the deadly duo? Find out in the next Chapter: Nagi Strikes!<br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
